<db:orgname class="corporation">The Qt Company Ltd.</db:orgname>
</db:author>
</db:authorgroup>
</db:info>
<db:para>Qt Quick Controls 2 provides a set of controls that can be used to build complete interfaces in Qt Quick.</db:para>
<db:section xml:id="prerequisites">
<db:title>Prerequisites</db:title>
<db:para>The <db:link xlink:href="qtquick-controls-qmlmodule2.xml">QML types</db:link> can be imported into your application using the following import statement in your <db:code>.qml</db:code> file:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">import QtQuick.Controls 2.0
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>The <db:link xlink:href="qtquickcontrols2-module.xml">C++ classes</db:link> can be included into your application using the following include statement:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">#include &lt;QtQuickControls2&gt;
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>To link against the corresponding C++ libraries, add the following to your qmake project file:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">QT += quickcontrols2
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>For more details, see <db:link xlink:href="qtquickcontrols2-gettingstarted.xml">Getting Started with Qt Quick Controls 2</db:link>.</db:para>
</db:section>
